column5: Hit Mitchell lake for the day, lot's of action for  this early in the season, with a lot of hits and follows. Brought home 5 pike including a 30"  and released 3 largies and a couple of panfish who decided to hit pike baits.  Water temps were mid 60's and spinnerbaits were the lure of choice. Would have limited but I lost a couple next to the boat.
nice! Oh how I wish I could target some pike in Zone 11 rigth now.
Nice fish! Can't wait to fish for some more pike again myself, this spring bite never really happened for me this year.
Got my car all loaded up! Can't wait
